heaviest_rainfall.status: The storm today is ranked 7th for the amount of rainfall recorded during one storm.  23.86mm fell at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour over 31.0 hours.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 2nd ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 27.6mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  6.1mm of rain fell during the storm's 2.6 hours length.  34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 7th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of31.0 hours.  It came with 23.86mm of rainfall, at times, falling at 8.3mm per hour.  A relentless rainstorm took place on 09 November 2025, it lasted 144.8 hours and it delivered 47.89mm of rain at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.
